25|$|The two {{operating}} concentrated {{solar power}} plants are the 1MW Saguaro <b>Solar</b> <b>Power</b> <b>Plant</b> completed in 2005, the first commercial CSP plant of the 3rd millennium, and a 5MW solar trough system at the University of Arizona Solar Tech Park project which was completed in 2011. The 280MW Solano Generating Station is under construction. The 1.5MW Maricopa <b>Solar</b> <b>Power</b> <b>Plant</b> completed in 2010, using Stirling dish technology, was decommissioned in September 2011 and sold at auction on April17, 2012 to CondiSys Solar Technology of China, for $250,000.|$|E
