40|$|We discuss {{separate}} and integrated approaches to building scalable <b>solar</b> <b>power</b> <b>plants</b> and wildlife sanctuaries. Both <b>solar</b> <b>power</b> <b>plants</b> and wildlife sanctuaries {{need a lot}} of land. We quantify some of the requirements using various estimates of the rate of <b>solar</b> <b>power</b> production as well as the rate of adding wildlife to a sanctuary over the time range 2010 - 2050. We use population dynamics equations to study the evolution of solar energy and tiger populations up to and beyond 2050. ...|$|R
